# Layer boundaries

## Import rules

| Layer | May import | Must NOT import |
|-------|------------|-----------------|
| `src/contracts/` | nothing game-specific | `src/games/`, app packages |
| `src/mcts/` | `src/contracts/` | `src/games/`, `src/coordinator/`, app packages |
| `src/coordinator/` | `src/contracts/`, `src/worker-port/` | `src/games/` (adapter passed in) |
| `src/worker/` | `src/contracts/`, `src/mcts/`, `src/games/` | coordinator, React, DOM |
| `src/games/<name>/` | `src/contracts/` | other games |

## Responsibility split

**MCTSEngine / worker**
- UCT loop, rollouts, tree nodes, `StopSignal` polling
- No `setTimeout`, no UI, no multi-phase chaining, no time budgets

**MCTSSearchCoordinator (main thread)**
- `computeMove`, thinking delay, `timeLimitMs`, multi-phase loop
- `stop()` / interrupted partial turns, parallel worker merge
- Progress aggregation for UI

**Game app**
- Calls `coordinator.computeMove()` and `coordinator.stop()` only
- Never calls `postSearch`, never talks to `Worker` directly

## Worker isolation

- Each worker: isolated tree, RNG (`SearchParameters.seed`), memory
- **No** locks, `SharedArrayBuffer`, or cross-worker postMessage
- Parallel results merged on the **main thread** by the coordinator only

## Functions over the wire

`SearchFunctions` are **not** sent via `postMessage`. Worker resolves them locally via `SearchParameters.heuristicId` and the game registry.
